There are some tribalistic people who believe what &quot;they think&quot; is contingent upon what other people want them to think and believe.  It is their way of gaining acceptance.  They have little regard for truth, reason, accuracy, fact, morals, values, traditions, etc.  In their moronic quest for acceptance they seek strength in numbers.  They become non-thinking, but politically correct... and they become a force to contend with.<br>
The squeaking wheel gets the grease... but is the squeaking wheel always the best wheel of the four?  Often not!<br>
Politicians... leaders of the politically correct...hold the grease bucket.  Most are moral whores, who will do anything for a vote..they are slaves to the press... slaves of sensationalism and squeakers.<br>
I wonder what would have happened if the total population would have stood up for our military involvement in Viet Nam.  Would the Communists have recognized a concerted effort and backed off?  Would the war have been short and sweet?  Would fewer Vietnamese and American have died?  Would the Vietnamese government have matured into a sound demoracy?  Would there not be millions of Americans with PTSD?  Could tens maybe hundreds of thousands of suicides, divorces, etc..been avoided?  I guess we will never KNOW!<br>
MTF
